      • ArrayIterator

        public ArrayIterator(T[] array)
              throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        The standard constructor takes an array as a parameter. If not specified through one of the other two constructors, the range will always be set to 0 - (array.lenght-1).
        Parameters:
        array - The array that will be iterated.
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An exception is thrown if the array is null or has no elements.

      • ArrayIterator

        public ArrayIterator(T[] array,
                     int startIndex)
              throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        The start position of the iterator can be specified with the startIndex parameter.
        Parameters:
        array - The array that will be iterated.
        startIndex - The starting position of the iterator.
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An exception is thrown if the array is null or has no elements, or if the startIndex is < 0, >= array.length, or > endIndex.

      • ArrayIterator

        public ArrayIterator(T[] array,
                     int startIndex,
                     int length)
              throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        The start and end positions of the iterator can be specified with the startIndex and length parameters.
        Parameters:
        array - The array that will be iterated.
        startIndex - The starting position of the iterator.
        length - The total number of elements that will be iterated.
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An exception is thrown if the array is null or empty, or startIndex < 0, startIndex >= array.length, or startIndex > endIndex, or endIndex < 0, endIndex >= array.length, or endIndex < startIndex.
